# Daemonizing Node apps

### Chapter 1: The Problem

So, you've got your project all done, palms sweating, waiting for your friends to try out your ligma ballz joke magnum opus website. You run `npm run build` and `npm run start` and voila - now you can't use your console anymore...

![Why won't my favourite commands run???](/unresponsive_console.png)
*Why won't my favourite commands run???*

### Chapter 2: The Solution

If you're a fellow christian - you should stop now. We're going to need help from the <span className="text-red-500 font-bold text-2xl">OTHER SIDEðŸ”¥ðŸ˜ˆ</span> to fix that problem. What am I talking about? The **DAEMONS!!!**

> In multitasking computer operating systems, a daemon is a computer program that runs as a background process, rather than being under the direct control of an interactive user.
>>  \- **John 3:16 (CSB)**

The one that came up first when I googled was pm2, which means it is definitely the best one.
Install it with `npm i pm2 -g` and run with `pm2 start npm -- *script you want to run*`. In my case, the script was **start**.
